{"source_key":"sha256-c8597aca71664a84bdd657ea13dadbd3","record_index":468,"record_hash":"sha256:79b1ccb1ceb23192904d42e34238c14d759908055fce58a518c1e9271a7dce21","timestamp":"2026-05-20T01:42:49.015Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 2e660d\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1843\nOutput:\n## Turn Data\n\nA turn needs an ID. The exact key shape is open, but the ID should be stable\nenough for idempotent repeated capture. Given a turn, it should be possible to\nfind the transcript records that were newly observed in that turn.\n\nTurn identity should be derived from capture content, not from time or provider\nturn ids. A good shape is:\n\n```text\nturn-key = hash(session_key + source_key + ordered_new_record_hashes)\n```\n\nThat makes the newly accepted transcript records the identity of what this\ncapture observed. Capture timestamp and environment snapshot are turn\nattributes, not identity. This also makes retries easier: the same accepted\nrecord set maps to the same turn key.\n\nProvider-native turn identifiers should not define the durable `turn-key`.\nProviders may omit them, define turns differently, expose private/raw ids, or\ninclude many provider turns inside one first-time backfill capture. If present,\nthey can be stored as optional record-level grouping metadata, preferably as a\nsafe provider turn key rather than a raw provider id.\n\nMinimum useful fields:\n\n- turn id\n- session key\n- source key\n- capture timestamp\n- transcript record membership, probably by record hash and/or source record\n  index\n- optional provider turn key on transcript records, for grouping/display only\n- optional previous turn reference, if it can be made meaningful\n- environment snapshot\n\nThe record membership matters because `but-agentlog` already deduplicates\nrecords. Without turn membership, repeated hook capture preserves the transcript\nbut erases the boundaries between capture invocations.\n\nThe model should distinguish:\n\n- **capture turn:** a stop-hook capture observation with new transcript records\n  and a repository environment snapshot\n- **provider turn:** a provider-native conversation grouping, such as a user\n  prompt and the resulting assistant/tool activity\n\nCapture turns are the durable agentlog concept. Provider\n[TRUNCATED]\ncords plus session/source metadata\n- `write_transcript_batch` filters records through `:record-hashes`\n- transcript records already carry `source_key`, `record_index`, and\n  `record_hash`\n\nThe missing piece is that `write_transcript_batch` throws away the batch\nboundary after appending records. A turn writer would need to receive the set of\nnewly accepted records and write a corresponding turn object.\n\n`but-agentlog` should probably become a higher-level GitButler crate for this\nfeature and depend on other `but-*` crates instead of reimplementing workspace\ninspection. The likely shape is:\n\n- depend on `but-ctx` so capture can build the same repository/workspace context\n  as the rest of GitButler\n- prefer reusable `but-api` entry points when they already provide the product\n  shape we need\n- use `but_api::diff::changes_in_worktree` or\n  `but_api::diff::changes_in_worktree_with_perm` for uncommitted worktree files\n- use `but_api::legacy::workspace::head_info` as the first stack/branch snapshot\n  source, even though it is under `legacy`, because it already wraps the\n  GitButler workspace model and returns the branch/stack view we need\n\nThis means the first implementation can capture environment snapshots from the\nsame APIs the app already trusts. If the legacy `head_info` dependency becomes\ntoo costly later, it can be replaced behind an agentlog-local snapshot adapter\nwithout changing the stored turn model.\n\nOne possible storage shape:\n\n```text\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:turns = list<TurnSummary JSON>\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:turn:<turn-key> = TurnDetail JSON\n```\n\nWhere `TurnSummary` is cheap to scan and `TurnDetail` contains record\nmembership plus the environment snapshot. The exact GitMeta representation needs\nchecking against list/set/record ergonomics.\n\n## Simplification Opportunity\n\nThis may also simplify deduplication conceptually:\n\n- record hashes answer \"have we stored this transcript record before?\"\n- turn membership answers \"which records were new in this capture invocation?\"\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T01:42:49.015Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}